3. NUMERICAL RESULTS

In this section we present some numerical results obtained with the proposed shell elements. The analysis problems studied have been selected to assess the predictive capabilities of the elements.
3.1. The patch test

The patch test has been widely used as a test for element convergence, despite its limitations for mixed formulations. We use the test here in numerical form to merely assess the sensitivity of our elements to geometric distortions.

